                <h1>Explore the Rich History of Vans: From Skate Shoes to Global Icon</h1>
                <p>Vans, founded in 1966 by Paul Van Doren and partners in California, started as a shoemaking company primarily for skateboarding and surf culture. The iconic "Off the Wall" tagline originated in the 1970s. Over the decades, Vans evolved into a global brand, becoming synonymous with youth culture, music, and extreme sports.</p>
